'''PT Bio Farma (Persero)''' is an Indonesian [[State-owned Enterprise in Indonesia|state-owned enterprise]] based in Bandung, Indonesia which produces vaccines and sera to support [[immunization]] in Indonesia and other countries. Bio Farma has entered into a pre-qualification list of the [[World Health Organization|World Health Organization (WHO)]]. Bio Farma vaccine produced [[vaccine]] consists of [[virus]] (vaccines against [[measles]], [[polio]] and [[hepatitis B]]), and bacterial vaccines (vaccine DTP vaccine TT, vaccines DT, and vaccine BCG). Bio Farma vaccines have supplied vaccines to multiple countries through [[UNICEF]], [[PAHO]] and other organizations.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.biofarma.co.id/profile/|title=Bio Farma profile  |date=June 6, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://bce.unpad.ac.id/pt-bio-farma/ |title=Bio Farma profile  |date=June 11, 2017}}</ref>

==History==

[[File:COLLECTIE TROPENMUSEUM s Lands Koepok Inrichting en het Instituut Pasteur exterieur van het gebouw Bandoeng. TMnr 60012974.jpg|thumb|right|Main Building of Bio Farma circa 1930]]

Bio Farma's history began during the [[Dutch East Indies]] period, when the colonial government founded {{lang|nl|Parc-vaccinogène}} (State Vaccine Development Agency) on 6 August 1890. The agency occupied a building in [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Weltevreden – Batavia]], which is now [[Gatot Soebroto Army Hospital]]. Since its inception, {{lang|nl|Parc-vaccinogène}} focused on eliminating [[Infection|infectious diseases]], which leads to its cooperation with [[Pasteur Institute]]. Eventually, the agency was renamed to {{lang|nl|Parc-vaccinogène en Instituut Pasteur}} in 1895.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.biofarma.co.id/en/sejarah-kami/|title=Sejarah PT Bio Farma (Persero)  |date=June 6, 2017}}</ref>

During the administration of [[Johan Paul van Limburg Stirum|J.P. van Limburg Stirum]], Hendrik Freerk Tillema recommended to move the capital of [[Dutch East Indies]] to Bandung  due to its natural conditions and hilly terrain, making it easier to defend. The idea was gradually accepted and began to be implemented by the Dutch colonial government in early 1920s after it was supported by Prof. J. Kolopper, Rector of [[Bandung Institute of Technology|''Technische Hoogeschool te Bandoeng'']] at the time. Government and private offices along with other agencies began moving to Bandung, including the foreign trade office, [[salvation army]], government bodies and {{lang|nl|Landskoepok Inrichling en Instituut Pasteur}}, which stayed in Bandung until the present day.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://safitriapcantik.wordpress.com/profil/ |title=Sejarah Bio Farma|date=June 11, 2017}}</ref>

The agency has experienced several changes in name and legal entity, which are as follows:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog-urangsunda.blogspot.co.id/2013/11/sejarah-berdirinya-biofarma-dok.html?m=1/ |title=Sejarah Bio Farma|date=June 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://elib.unikom.ac.id/files/disk1/485/jbptunikompp-gdl-taufiknugr-24217-1-unikom_t-i.pdf |title=Sejarah dan Perkembangan PT Bio Farma (Persero)|date=June 12, 2017}}</ref>

[[File:Bio Farma Bandung.jpg|thumb|right|Main Building of Bio Farma (2005)]]

* 1890-1895{{spaced ndash}}    {{lang|nl|Parc-vaccinogène}}
* 1895-1901{{spaced ndash}}    {{lang|nl|Parc-vaccinogène en Instituut Pasteur}}
