The '''Business in Gaming Conference''' ('''BiG''') is an annual game convention hosted and organized by students in the [[MIT Sloan School of Management]] in [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]]. The conference "seeks to bring together industry leaders, game developers, professors and students from leading MBA institutions such as MIT and Harvard to discuss the future of the gaming industry." <ref name="about">[http://www.mitbig.com/?page_id=2 Business in Gaming Conference >> About] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090417065505/http://www.mitbig.com/?page_id=2 |date=April 17, 2009 }}</ref>

The first convention took place on May 8, 2009. The opening address was delivered by Christopher Weaver, the founder of [[Bethesda Softworks]] and current MIT professor. Keynotes included [[Ken Levine (video game designer)|Ken Levine]], the founder of [[2K Boston/2K Australia]] and Susan Bonds, the CEO of [[42 Entertainment]].  Panels covered topics such as In Game Advertising, Digital Distribution, MMO Business Models, and Serious Games.  Panelists included [[Curt Schilling]], Founder of [[38 Studios]]; Jon Phenix of [[GamerDNA]]; Craig Alexander of [[Turbine, Inc.]]; Robert Ferrari of [[Sanrio Digital]]; Eugene Evans of [[Mythic Entertainment]]; published authors Ethan Mollick and David Edery; Doug Whatley, CEO of [[BreakAway Games]]; Bruce Roberts of [[BBN Technologies]]; Matthew Bellows of [[Vivox]]; Albert Reed, founder of [[Demiurge Studios]]; John Rizzo, CEO of [[Zeebo]].<ref name="speakers">[http://www.mitbig.com/?page_id=5 Business in Gaming Conference >> Speakers] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090617005141/http://www.mitbig.com/?page_id=5 |date=June 17, 2009 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.joystiq.com/2009/04/13/ken-levine-keynoting-first-mit-business-in-gaming-conference/ "Ken Levine keynoting first MIT 'Business in Gaming' conference"]</ref><ref>[http://www.gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=23174 "MIT Business In Gaming Conf Adds Levine, Schilling"]</ref><ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS65972+13-Apr-2009+BW20090413 "MIT Sloan to host its first ever Business in Gaming Conference on May 8, 2009"]</ref><ref>[http://www.gamedaily.com/articles/news/bioshock-creator-speaking-at-mit-gaming-business-conference/?biz=1 "BioShock Creator Speaking at MIT Gaming Business Conference"]</ref><ref>[http://www.masshightech.com/stories/2009/05/11/daily5-MIT-gaming-conference-Schilling-calls-out-lack-of-gaming-sales-metrics.html "MIT gaming conference: Schilling calls out lack of gaming sales metrics"]</ref>

