'''Donald Black''' was a British businessman and accountant in Hong Kong. Black was a partner of the [[KPMG|Peat, Marwick, Mitchell & Co.]] until he retired in March 1962.<ref>{{cite book|page=427|title=The Accountant, Volume 146, Part 2|publisher=Lafferty Publications|year=1962}}</ref> He was appointed provisionally to the [[Legislative Council of Hong Kong|Legislative Council]] as an [[unofficial member]] during the absence of [[Hugh Barton]] from July to November 1960.<ref>{{cite book|page=403|title=Hong Kong: Report|author=Great Britain. Colonial Office|publisher=Government Press|year=1961}}</ref>

