'''Pan African Chamber of Commerce and Industry''' (PACCI) is a business support body representing national [[Chambers of Commerce]] and private businesses from across the continent. Re-incorporated in March 2010, the PACCI has the status of an [[international nongovernmental organization]].<ref name=Governance>{{cite web|title=Governance|url=http://www.pacci.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=9&Itemid=5|publisher=PACCI|accessdate=23 February 2013}}</ref> The PACCI works with international organizations, [[News media|media entities]], [[policy-makers]] and through its [[List of Pan African Chamber of Commerce and Industry members|national member chambers]] with [[Africa]]n national governments, to help African businesses to foster [[Economic development|sustainable]] [[economic growth]], [[entrepreneurship]] and [[prosperity]].<ref name="About PACCI">{{cite web|title=About PACCI|url=http://www.pacci.org/index.php/about-us|publisher=PACCI|accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref>

The PACCI is based in [[Addis Ababa]], [[Ethiopia]], home of the [[African Union]] and the [[United Nations]] [[Economic Commission for Africa|United Nations Economic Commission for Africa]].<ref name="About PACCI"/> {{As of|2017|February}}, Kebour Ghenna serves as the Executive Director.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201702250081.html|title=Africa: Why Africans Less Trade Among Themselves?|last=Teshome|first=Mengisteab|date=2017-02-25|work=The Ethiopian Herald |access-date=2017-04-10}}</ref>

