'''Susana Palazuelos de Wichtendahl''' (born c. 1935), alternatively known as '''Susanna Palazuelos''', is a well-known Mexican chef and wedding organizer.<ref>http://www.univision.com/estilo-de-vida/cocina/receta-de-la-chef-susanna-palazuelos</ref> She is also a book writer, having written cook books such as "Mexico the Beautiful: Authentic Recipes from the Regions of Mexico"<ref>http://www.abebooks.com/book-search/isbn/000215949x/</ref> and "Mexican Favorites".<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Susanna-Palazuelos/e/B000APHL4I</ref>
[[File:Susanna Palazuelos.jpg|thumb|150px|right|Susana Palazuelos with her son Eduardo Palazuelos]]
In 1977, Palazuelos opened a restaurant in her native [[Acapulco]], named "Banquetes Susana Palazuelos". She is the owner and general director of the restaurant.<ref>http://www.therealtravelexperience.com/speakers/susanna-palazuelos/</ref>
During her career, Palazuelos, considered by some to be the creator of outdoor weddings in [[Mexico]], has cooked for royalty, including the king of [[Malaysia]] and [[Queen Elizabeth II]].<ref>http://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/after-office/susanna-palazuelos-su-cocina-hace-suenos-realidad.html</ref>
Susana has a son, Eduardo Palazuelos, a renowned chef from Mexico and the owner of the restaurants Zibu (Acapulco) and [http://www.mardelzur.com/ '''<big>Mar del Zur</big>'''] (Monterrey).<ref>http://www.mardelzur.com/</ref>
She is the aunt of famous actor [[Roberto Palazuelos]], who considers her to be his real mother, as she raised him.<ref>http://www.unioncancun.mx/articulo/2014/07/09/espectaculos/roberto-palazuelos-cuestiona-aparicion-de-su-mama</ref> ==External links== {{Reflist}}
